1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:16,672
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambuddhassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambuddhassa

2
00:00:16,652 --> 00:00:33,676
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambuddhassa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:33,695 --> 00:00:40,646
The word I'd like to tackle tonight is this word āvijja.

4
00:00:40,665 --> 00:00:42,128
It's one of these core words.

5
00:00:42,148 --> 00:00:46,152
Ā means not and vijja means knowledge.

6
00:00:46,301 --> 00:01:12,310
and it's translated unfortunately as ignorance but the word ignorance has a sort of pejorative feel about it like you're stupid or you're culpable but this is just basically not knowing I did come across a word in the dictionary and I thought I might use that but I don't think everybody knows it so it's this quality of not knowing right at the beginning

7
00:01:13,977 --> 00:01:15,838
I mean, what do we know as children?

8
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:18,402
You know, as a baby, what do we know?

9
00:01:18,421 --> 00:01:21,125
We don't know anything.

10
00:01:22,147 --> 00:01:23,447
And then it all piles in.

11
00:01:24,269 --> 00:01:35,102
The culture, the language, the habits of your parents, of our parents, you know, and then the school and everything just piles in.

12
00:01:36,102 --> 00:01:40,608
And is it any wonder that we presume that this is what we are?

13
00:01:40,628 --> 00:01:43,191
This is definitely, phenomenally what we are, you see.

14
00:01:44,048 --> 00:02:01,347
But let me give you an example of what this ignorance is, because what it does is, it presumes, it's not a, we've got to be careful here, it's not an evil thing, it's just a simple matter of, well, this must be right.

15
00:02:02,576 --> 00:02:07,783
I had a hut in the monastery I was at.

16
00:02:07,802 --> 00:02:08,643
I call it a kuti.

17
00:02:09,544 --> 00:02:11,787
A hut, unfortunately, doesn't give you the right impression.

18
00:02:11,826 --> 00:02:18,014
It was a proper brick-built little building with its own toilet.

19
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:25,381
And one year, somehow these little flies came in called a hopatua.

20
00:02:25,401 --> 00:02:26,483
Tiny little flies.

21
00:02:27,783 --> 00:02:31,587
And the disturbing thing about them was that they got through the mosquito net.

22
00:02:32,733 --> 00:02:39,163
And when they bit, they left this little pimple with itches for about three days, or it did for me.

23
00:02:39,183 --> 00:02:46,395
And it sort of slowly drives you mad, even though you're meditating, it slowly drives you mad.

24
00:02:46,616 --> 00:02:52,766
And I used to regularly evict all the spiders from my room.

25
00:02:53,978 --> 00:02:56,762
But then it occurred to me that, no, I need these spiders.

26
00:02:56,782 --> 00:02:59,626
They, in fact, would eat these flies.

27
00:03:00,907 --> 00:03:02,710
So I allowed the spiders to come in.

28
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:08,519
And I ended up with lots of these spider webs, and some of them were big spiders.

29
00:03:08,538 --> 00:03:14,567
And to my horror, the place got more and more filled with these little flies.

30
00:03:15,127 --> 00:03:19,713
And it came to a point when I was actually considering leaving and going to another monastery.

31
00:03:19,735 --> 00:03:20,795
It was just becoming unbearable.

32
00:03:22,210 --> 00:03:30,379
And there was another monk in the western room, a Canadian, staying at the monastery, been there for longer than me.

33
00:03:31,540 --> 00:03:36,926
And he came along one day and I told him, I said, you know, I'm on the point of leaving.

34
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,790
I can't handle these flies.

35
00:03:39,811 --> 00:03:43,235
And he looked around and he said, it's these cobwebs.

36
00:03:44,036 --> 00:03:45,197
They breed on cobwebs.

37
00:03:48,855 --> 00:03:58,224
So I of course immediately evicted all the spiders and the whole situation and burnt Josh sticks and the whole situation became bearable again.

38
00:03:58,245 --> 00:04:08,153
But that for me was a prime example of what happens when you don't know and you presume and you end up with more suffering than you expected.

39
00:04:09,455 --> 00:04:18,423
So this Awidya, this Awidya that we suffer from is just a very simple state of not knowing.

40
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:28,475
And then we move into this position of given knowledge and there's a presumption that this is what we are, what I believe, this is me, this is mine.

41
00:04:30,538 --> 00:04:36,867
And it's a mistake, it's just a mistake.

42
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:52,461
And because we begin from that position of not knowing, from an intellectual or from an understanding point of view, from the heart's point of view we begin from a position of innocence.

43
00:04:52,482 --> 00:04:56,189
So it's just a mistake, an innocent mistake.

44
00:04:56,726 --> 00:05:05,281
But unfortunately, it does end up with depression, anxiety, guilt, shame, and all the rest of the whole gamut of human suffering.

45
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:08,745
And at some point, one says, I've got to meditate.

46
00:05:08,766 --> 00:05:12,451
So you end up in a meditation hall trying to get rid of this stuff.

47
00:05:12,471 --> 00:05:17,519
And then the process comes back on itself, you see, the process comes back on itself, where you realize...

48
00:05:18,057 --> 00:05:27,692
You know, as you go deeper and deeper into yourself, you're getting close to the original mistake, which is to do with an identity, an identity of being a human being.

49
00:05:28,413 --> 00:05:29,314
That's what we think we are.

50
00:05:31,096 --> 00:05:34,682
As we undo that, you see, there are two processes going on.

51
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,187
The process of vipassana is a process of understanding where the mistake lies.

52
00:05:40,447 --> 00:05:57,649
So that's why we're looking at this business of impermanence, the business of how we relate to things by way of grasping or owning, wanting and identifying, and how we have a deeper identity with what we're experiencing.

53
00:05:59,502 --> 00:06:03,687
And by undoing that, we're beginning to understand what we really are.

54
00:06:04,468 --> 00:06:10,754
But the other process that's going on is that we're having to deal with all these emotional states that come up.

55
00:06:11,757 --> 00:06:24,091
And we begin to realize that by just allowing them to express themselves as mental states, as emotional states, they're actually exhausting themselves.

56
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:27,314
That's why we come off the dream, because it's through dreams that they develop.

57
00:06:28,713 --> 00:06:35,560
And so these two processes of the understanding is undermining this original mistake.

58
00:06:36,862 --> 00:06:48,055
And the process of purification is undermining and going back upon the product of that mistake, even though it was done innocently.

59
00:06:48,076 --> 00:06:53,843
So the end process that we're moving towards is a point of understanding, which we call wisdom.

60
00:06:54,817 --> 00:06:59,908
And from the heart's point of view, the purification takes us back to the beginning of that innocence.

61
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:03,735
But it's now not an ignorant and not knowing innocence.

62
00:07:03,915 --> 00:07:09,526
It's now a wisdom within a purified heart, an immaculate heart.

63
00:07:09,547 --> 00:07:12,372
And that's the end of the process when we reach death.

64
00:07:13,499 --> 00:07:21,372
So the process that we're going through, or have been through, is from a point of ignorance into a mistake which has caused us problems.

65
00:07:22,413 --> 00:07:26,341
And we undo those problems and come to a point of wisdom.

66
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:37,920
From the heart's point of view, we've innocently made a mistake, and we have all the problems that come from that mistake, including guilt and shame and all that,

67
00:07:38,507 --> 00:07:42,517
And then as we undermine that, we return to a purified heart.

68
00:07:43,158 --> 00:07:48,872
This purified heart is then an energy, a form of energy, which then reconnects with the world.

69
00:07:49,894 --> 00:07:51,658
And that reconnection we call love.

70
00:07:53,663 --> 00:07:56,971
And that love has its various forms of compassion and joy.

71
00:08:00,276 --> 00:08:24,141
so we should be hopeful we should live we should practice with joy knowing that there is an end to this process so I hope my words have been of some use to you may you be fully liberated sooner rather than later

